      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHOWTIME SHADOW (2) won his Maiden comfortably over 1100m at Gosford first-up, then went close over 1300m at Hawkesbury. Fitter again and should be in a prominent position throughout. Has scope for further improvement and can bounce back. IS IT SPECTACULAR (1) resumed in good order at Canterbury for the new stable and then tackled the Listed Canberra Guineas over 1400m, beaten 3.2L. Much better placed today, and he still has plenty in the tank. EMALYN (4) led last start over 1300m at Newcastle, beaten 1.2 lengths. She was a big Maiden winner there at her sole third-up outing and can run a bold race. WISNIERSKA (3) has needed her two runs this preparation. Raced mostly in Queensland last time in and showed enough to consider today. Maps well and has the blinkers on again. OLIVIA TWIST (5) led and deserved her Maiden win at Gosford as a $3 favourite and can build on that.",
